{"descriptions":[{"id":1122,"title":"Sechung Introduction","content":"\u003cdiv class=\"essay-body\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"essay-head2\"\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"chapter\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eAntiquities of Zhang Zhung\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"author\"\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003eby \u003c/span\u003eJohn Vincent Bellezza\u003c!--(a)--\u003e\u003cbr/\u003eEdited by Geoffrey Barstow and Mickey Stockwell \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"width: 100%; text-align: right;\" align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"copyright\"\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003e Copyright \u0026copy;  2010. \u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"\" id=\"permission\"\u003e\n\u003cbr/\u003eReproduced with permission from the author \u003cbr/\u003eunder the \u003ca href=\"/tools/licenses.php#essay=/thl/text-license/\" class=\"thl-poplink\"\u003eTHL Digital Text License\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"b2-2\"\u003eII.2. Superficial structures: Primarily funerary superstructure\u003c/h2\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3 id=\"b2-2-23\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eSechung\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eSe chung\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/h3\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch4 id=\"b2-2-23-1\"\u003eBasic site data\u003c/h4\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cul class=\"bullet-blue\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eSite name: \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eSechung\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eSe chung\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eSite number: D-63\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eSite typology: II.2x \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eGeographic coordinate (N. lat.): 31\u0026ordm; 09.1\u0026#900; \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eGeographic coordinate (E. long.): 81\u0026ordm; 44.0\u0026#900; \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eElevation: 4390 m \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eAdministrative location (township): \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;ntser\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon \u0026rsquo;tsher\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eAdministrative location (county): \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eGar\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eSgar\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eSurvey expedition: HTCE\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eSurvey date: May 11, 2002\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eContemporary usage: None \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003eIdentifiable Buddhist constructions: None. \u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/ul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch4 id=\"b2-2-23-2\"\u003eGeneral site characteristics\u003c/h4\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eAccording to the monks of \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003ePretapuri\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003ePre ta pu ri\u003c/span\u003e, two\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\twooden coffins with human remains were discovered near \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eSechung\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eSe chung\u003c/span\u003e. These coffins occupied a large recess in an earthen bluff that rises above a wash. This site\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tis situated is a zone of dissected tablelands located between the \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eKand\u0026eacute; Chu\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eDkar \u0026rsquo;ded chu\u003c/span\u003e and two hills known as \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eRi Lhunpo\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eRi lhun po\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eSechung\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eSe chung\u003c/span\u003e. At the time of the survey, it was discovered that the hole ostensibly containing the coffins\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thad caved in. No structural evidence associated with burials is visible on the surface. The use of wooden coffins\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tseems to point to a different culture and/or period than that associated with the \u0026lsquo;\u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon\u003c/span\u003e\u0026rsquo; cist burials. \u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eIn the last 25 to 35 years, the \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eAli Tangkha\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eA li thang kha\u003c/span\u003eplain, which is bounded by the \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eKand\u0026eacute; Chu\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eDkar \u0026rsquo;ded chu\u003c/span\u003e, has been brought back into cultivation. Farmers of this locale report that corpses of the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u0026lsquo;\u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon\u003c/span\u003e\u0026rsquo; have been unearthed during plowing.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eAli Tangkha\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eA li thang kha\u003c/span\u003e is part of \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;ntser\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon \u0026rsquo;tsher\u003c/span\u003e (Abandoned \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon\u003c/span\u003e Lands), a region of western Tibet well known for its so-called \u003cspan class=\"popular\"\u003eM\u0026ouml;n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"scholar\"\u003eMon\u003c/span\u003e legacy. \u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctable cellspacing=\"8\" align=\"center\" class=\"navarrows\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"leftcell\"\u003e\n\u003ca class=\"backarrow\" title=\"Previous Section\"\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-left.gif\" title=\"Previous Section\"/\u003e\n\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"midcell\"\u003e\n\u003ca class=\"uparrow\" title=\"Beginning of Article\"\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-up.gif\" title=\"Beginning of Article\"/\u003e\n\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"rightcell\"\u003e\n\u003ca class=\"forwardarrow\" title=\"Next Section\"\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-right.gif\" title=\"Next Section\"/\u003e\n\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"chap-id\"\u003e/bellezza2/b2-2-23/\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"overflow: hidden; height: 300px;\" class=\"jqmWindow\" id=\"chapRefWindow\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"closebtn\"\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"#\"\u003eClose\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"height: 280px;\" class=\"conx-content\"\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eNote Citation for Page \u003cspan class=\"pgnm\"/\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"biblref\"\u003eJohn Vincent Bellezza, Antiquities of Zhang Zhung: A Comprehensive Inventory of Pre-Buddhist Archaeological Monuments on\n\t\t\t\t\tthe Tibetan Upland\n\t\t\t\t(Charlottesville, VA 22904:Tibetan \u0026amp; Himalayan Library, \n\t\t\t\t2010), \n\t\t\t\t\u003cspan class=\"pgnm\"/\u003e.\n\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eBibliographic Citation\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJohn Vincent Bellezza. Antiquities of Zhang Zhung: A Comprehensive Inventory of Pre-Buddhist Archaeological Monuments on\n\t\t\t\t\tthe Tibetan Upland, . \n\t\t\t\tCharlottesville, VA 22904:Tibetan \u0026amp; Himalayan Library, 2010.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e","source_url":"/places/culturalgeography/publications/bellezza-sites.php#book=/bellezza2/wb/b2-2-23","is_primary":false,"created_at":"2010-08-25 11:12:33 UTC","updated_at":"2010-08-25 11:12:33 UTC","authors":[]}]}